Description: The fastest parallel gzip
 Gzippy is a high-performance parallel gzip implementation written in Rust.
 It beats gzip and pigz by leveraging multiple CPU cores, SIMD instructions,
 and optimized compression libraries (libdeflate, zlib-ng).
 .
 Features:
  - Drop-in gzip replacement with compatible CLI
  - Parallel compression using all available cores
  - Memory-mapped I/O for zero-copy file access
  - Compatible output that works with all standard gzip tools
 .
 This package provides the gzippy and ungzippy commands.

